```

### Optional Service Pattern

```typescript
// src/env.ts — optional Zod schema
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY: z.string().optional(),

// src/env.ts — service availability helper
export const services = {
  stripe: Boolean(env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY),
} as const;

// Usage: gracefully skip when unconfigured
if (!services.stripe) {
  logger.info('Stripe not configured, skipping');
  return null;
}
```

## Do NOT Touch Without Review

These files affect every request and should not be modified without careful review:

| File | Why |
|---|---|
| `src/middleware.ts` | Controls auth for every route. Wrong config = security hole or broken app. |
| `src/lib/auth/get-auth.ts` | Dual-mode auth resolver. Breaking this breaks all authenticated endpoints. |
| `src/env.ts` | Environment validation. Breaking this prevents the app from starting. |
| `src/lib/db/schema.ts` | Database schema. Changes require migration planning. |
| `src/lib/api-response.ts` | Response envelope. Changing shape breaks all API consumers. |
| `drizzle.config.ts` | Database connection config. |
| `.github/workflows/ci.yml` | CI pipeline. Breaking this means broken PRs go undetected. |

